HEADWORD: Skeletonizer
<hw>Skel"e*ton*i`zer</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Any small moth whose larva eats the parenchyma of leaves, leaving
the skeleton; <as>as, the apple-leaf
<ex>skeletonizer</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
